stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource attending a lecture stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource an office of science user facility seminar series home about the seminar series attending a lecture past lectures maps & directions home attending a lecture the lectures take place every wednesday at 3 00 pm in slac's building 901 redtail hawk conference room every presentation will be preceded by 15 minutes of informal discussion over cookies and coffee and will be followed by time for anyone in the audience to share recent results or exciting experimental techniques if you have a slac badge please bring it with you to make passing through gate 17 on your way to building 901 easier if you do not have a badge please meet samira baradaran at gate 17 at 2 50 pm she will escort you through the gate and to the lecture slac is located at 2575 sand hill road menlo park ca 94025 please visit our maps and directions page for driving directions to the laboratory if you have specific questions or concerns about attending a lecture please contact samira baradaran share printer friendly version send to friend send to friend the stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource is a directorate of slac national accelerator laboratory which is operated by stanford university for the department of energy other news sources slac today ssrl headlines symmetry magazine lightsources org interactions org ilc newsline spires slac national accelerator laboratory slac national accelerator laboratory menlo park ca operated by stanford university for the us department of energy office of science content owner cathy knotts privacy notice security notice and terms of use doe stanford university
